        |
        +--&gt; Tutankhamun
                |
                +--&gt; Tomb discovery (1922)
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Invention of Writing System

::: .row

::: .col-12 .col-md-6

The Egyptians developed an early writing system. In the beginning, they expressed thoughts through `drawings and pictures`. Each picture represented a symbol or letter.

This picture-based script is called `Hieroglyphics`. The Greek word “Hieroglyphics” means `sacred writing`. They also made a type of paper using the bark of a reed plant called `Papyrus`.

:::

::: .col-12 .col-md-6

![img](https://t3.ftcdn.net/jpg/03/24/54/80/360_F_324548043_rq5Cd0OTg0cVJ4QABFEnJOkVVBY0Dbdu.jpg)

:::

:::

```text id="xjfsyl"
Writing System
        |
        +--&gt; Picture-based writing
        |
        +--&gt; Hieroglyphics
        |       |
        |       +--&gt; Sacred writing
        |
        +--&gt; Papyrus (paper)
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Science

::: .row

::: .col-12 .col-md-6

The Egyptians were the first to introduce a calendar system based on `12 months in a year` and `30 days in a month`.<br>
Since Pharaohs were believed to rule in the afterlife, Egyptian scientists developed techniques to preserve dead bodies from decay.<br>
This led to the invention of `mummification`, a process used to prevent decomposition and preserve the body for the afterlife.

:::

::: .col-12 .col-md-6

![img](https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/thumbnails/012/249/637/small/philadelphia-usa-april-27-2017-egyptian-newborn-baby-mummy-detail-free-photo.JPG)

:::

:::

```text id="xjfsyl"
Science
        |
        +--&gt; Time Calculation
        |       |
        |       +--&gt; 1 year = 12 months
        |       +--&gt; 1 month = 30 days
        |
        +--&gt; Mummification
                |
                +--&gt; Body preservation
```
</md></sn><sn><md>#### Facts About Egypt

1. Ancient Egyptian civilization developed along the `Nile River`.
2. The *Nile River* was the main `source of agriculture` and life in Egypt.
3. Egyptian civilization is one of the `oldest civilizations` in the world.
4. The early Egyptian period is called the `Pre-Dynastic` Period.
5. Ancient Egypt was divided into small city-states called `Nomes`.
6. Pharaohs were considered both `kings and divine rulers`.
7. Egyptians believed in life after death.
8. *Pyramids* were built as `tombs for Pharaohs`.
9. The Pyramid of `Khufu` is the `largest` pyramid in Egypt.
10. The `Sphinx` has the `body of a lion` and the `head of a Pharaoh`.
11. Egyptians used a *writing system* called `Hieroglyphics`.
12. Hieroglyphics means `sacred writing`
13. `Papyrus` was used by Egyptians to make paper-like material.
14. `Akhenaten` promoted the worship of a `single god Aten`.
15. *Akhenaten* is considered one of the `earliest monotheistic reformers`.
16. Egyptians developed a `calendar of 12 months` and `30 days per month`.
17. Mummification was used to preserve dead bodies.
18. *Tutankhamun’s tomb* was discovered in `1922`.
19. `Howard Carter` discovered the tomb of Tutankhamun.
20. Egyptian sculpture often represented gods, Pharaohs, and animals symbolically.
